==English==

===Adjective===
'''powdery'''

# Of or pertaining to [[powder]].
#:'''1872''' ''We were plowing through great deeps of '''powdery''' alkali dust that rose in thick clouds and floated across the plain like smoke from a burning house. We were coated with it like millers; so were the coach, the mules, the mail-bags, the driver -- we and the sage-brush and the other scenery were all one monotonous color.'' — Mark Twain, ''Roughing It'', [http://etext.virginia.edu/etcbin/ot2www-pubeng?specfile=/texts/english/modeng/publicsearch/modengpub.o2w&act=surround&offset=153632345&tag=EAF504&query=+powdery&id=eaf504 Chapter 21.]

